---
import HiddenCurrent from "@layouts/HiddenCurrent.astro";
import Logo from "@components/hidden-current/partials/Logo.svelte";
---

<HiddenCurrent title="Hidden Current">
  <div class="flex min-h-screen flex-col items-center px-4 py-24">
    <section class="flex max-w-xl flex-col gap-12">
      <div class="flex flex-row justify-center">
        <Logo />
      </div>
      <header class="flex w-full flex-row items-center justify-between">
        <h2 class="text-primary text-2xl font-black">Methodology</h2>
        <span class="text-body text-xs">Last updated: April 2026</span>
      </header>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 text-sm text-pretty">
        <h3 class="text-primary text-base font-bold">How it's calculated.</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Hidden Current</strong> estimates the energy and water used by each Claude response
          based on the length of the text it generates.
        </p>
        <p>
          Character count is converted to an estimated token count - the unit AI models use
          internally to process text. From there, published energy figures for modern GPU hardware
          are applied to arrive at a watt-hour estimate, then converted to water using the
          industry-standard Water Usage Effectiveness (WUE) figure of 1.9 litres per kWh.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-primary text-base font-bold">In short</h3>
        <p class="italic">
          Energy (Wh) = (input tokens &#x0078; 0.0001) + (output tokens &#x0078; 0.0003) + 0.002
          <br />
          Water (mL) = Energy &#x0078; 1,900
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>These are estimates</strong>. AI companies don't publish per-query consumption
          data, and the true figure varies depending on which data centre handles a request, the
          hardware it runs on, and local conditions like climate and cooling systems. The numbers
          are based on the best publicly available research, but should be read as informed
          approximations rather than precise measurements.
        </p>
        <p>The goal isn't precision - it's visibility.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</HiddenCurrent>
